data.enText: the top part of a hill or wave

data.chText: 正在浪峰上冲浪的运动员
data.enText: surfers riding the crest of the wave

data.chText: （尤指象征历史悠久家族、机构等的）饰章，纹章
data.enText: a design used as the symbol of a particular family, organization, etc., especially one that has a long history
a group of feathers that stand up on top of a bird's head

data.chText: 顶峰时期；极其成功；春风得意
data.enText: a situation in which sb is very successful, happy, etc.
to enjoy great success or support because of a particular situation or event

data.chText: 乐队正处于最近这次巡回演出后的顶峰状态。
data.enText: The band is riding the crest of its last tour.
to reach the top of a hill, mountain or wave

data.chText: 当他们到达山脊时，他放慢了步伐。
data.enText: He slowed the pace as they crested the ridge.
to reach its highest level before it falls again
The level of debt crested at a massive $290 billion in 1992.

means: (尤指象征历史悠久家族、机构等的)饰章，纹章

synonyms.bx: 由金属或其他材料制成，表明身份、职衔、所支持的团体等。
用布制成，缝在军人或警察制服的袖子上，表明佩戴者的军衔或警衔。
常印于银器、盘碟或信笺上，象征某一家族、机构等的历史悠久。

ex.enText: The thistle is the emblem of Scotland.

synonyms.bx: 通常用于代表国家、团体等。

ex.chText: 她佩戴了一枚钻石胸针。

synonyms.bx: 指佩戴在胸前作为饰件的胸针，或带有别针的徽章，作后者解时尤用于美国英语。

d.text: 饰针，胸针；（背面有别针的）徽章

tips.tip: 英国英语中用 brooch 表示“胸针”。

data.chText: 顶峰时期；极其成功；春风得意
data.enText: a situation in which sb is very successful, happy, etc.
to enjoy great success or support because of a particular situation or event

data.chText: 乐队正处于最近这次巡回演出后的顶峰状态。
data.enText: The band is riding the crest of its last tour.

tr: a showy growth of e.g. feathers or skin on the head of a bird or other animal
(heraldry) in medieval times, an emblem used to decorate a helmet
the center of a cambered road
the top line of a hill, mountain, or wave
the top or extreme point of something (usually a mountain or hill)
example: the view from the peak was magnificent
they clambered to the tip of Monadnock
the region is a few molecules wide at the summit

value.def: The crest of a hill or a wave is the top of it.

defx.def: If you say that you are on the crest of a wave, you mean that you are feeling very happy and confident because things are going well for you.
defx.tran: 春风得意;处于巅峰时期

example.ex: The band are riding on the crest of a wave with the worldwide success of their number one selling single.
example.tran: 该乐队正处于巅峰时期，单曲唱片销量世界排名第一。

value.def: When someone crests a hill, they reach the top of it.

example.ex: The first wave of marchers crested the hill.
example.tran: 第一批游行示威者登上了山顶。

value.def: A bird's crest is a group of upright feathers on the top of its head.

example.ex: Both birds had a dark blue crest.
example.tran: 两种鸟都长着深蓝色的羽冠。

value.def: A crest is a design that is the symbol of a noble family, a town, or an organization.

example.ex: On the wall is the family crest.
example.tran: 墙上挂着那个家族的饰章。

value.tran: (贵族家庭、城镇或组织的)饰章，纹章
